courses.course_syllabus:
This is a research-oriented graduate level course on research methodology. There are four major objectives of this course:

(1) It discusses the nature of scientific quantitative survey research methods;

(2) It introduces to graduate students common quantitative statistical techniques used in management survey research;

(3) It familiarizes students with key methodological concerns when conducting management research using surveys;

(4) It provides students with hand-on knowledge on statistical packages and how they are used in survey-based management research.
